column5: Got to do some chain saw work this weekend. Bought fresh premium gas. My Stihl oil that came with the saw  in small containers is 3-4 yrs old. Is there a shelf life on this stuff?
As long as the container has been sealed tight, as to no moister getting in (Milky colour) the oil should be fine. Give the bottle a good shake and have a look see.  Dan.
Stihl oil even has stabilizer already in it.. so it shouldn't go bad. Have never had an issue with it, even mixed and sitting for a couple of years running it in my saws.
